Nigeria’s Labor Unions Stop Planned Strike After Agreement With Government

-- B y   D u l u e   M b a c h u
-- 
2011-07-20T06:02:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/nigeria-s-labor-unions-stop-planned-strike-after-agreement-with-government.html
Nigeria ’s two main labor federations
stopped a planned three-day strike today after they reached an
agreement with the government on payment of the minimum wage.  The government and the unions have agreed that the new wage
structure signed into law by President Goodluck Jonathan in
March will take effect from August, Abdulwaheed Umar of the
Nigerian Labour Congress and Peter Esele of the Trade Union
Congress, said in Abuja today in a joint statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net  